cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.IR, cs.HC

This paper involves the analysis of log data using non-negative matrix factorization techniques to reveal dependencies among various factors related to student activity in an online educational system. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as well as computational methods for data analysis (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper deals with educational systems (cs.CE) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves tracking behavioral changes of individual students over time. Finally, the paper also touches upon human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as it aims to optimize the learning experience and improve performance.
